  "title": "Ohio Spent a Week Chasing a White Peacock Through the Suburbs",
  "script": "Escaped bird? In Ohio? A white peahen — a female peacock — went rogue through Parma Heights, Ohio after escaping from her owner. She was being shipped to Florida. Instead she spent days flying around Cuyahoga County, landing on rooftops, outrunning animal control like she had somewhere to be. Brooklyn and Parma Heights Animal Control caught her on camera behind a house on Beverly Drive — and she flew away. She came back. They tried again. Eventually they caught her Tuesday night. The owner is getting their peahen back, and presumably trying Florida again with a better carrier. But just to be clear — someone lost a fully white peacock for an entire week. Who loses a white peahen like that?",
